body:
I think the following is a correct usage of with operator to cast type for queue sum

```
    /* verilator lint_off WIDTH */
    byte myqueue [$] = {2,-1,127};
    int total;
    initial begin
        total = myqueue.sum() with (int'(item));
        $display("%d",total );
    end
    /* verilator lint_on WIDTH */
```
however its generating an internal error in Verilator 4.221 devel rev v4.220-25-g7bfc1a00 compiled from master branch of this repo

```
verilator -Wall --trace -cc testbench.sv e1/DUT.sv --exe main.cpp --top-module testbench -CFLAGS "-DTIMEOUT=100" -Wno-UNUSED
%Error: Internal Error: e1/DUT.sv:42:31: ../V3LinkDot.cpp:397: Module/etc never assigned a symbol entry?
   42 |         total = myqueue.sum() with (int'(item));
      |                               ^~~~
                        ... See the manual at https://verilator.org/verilator_doc.html for more assistance.
make: *** [Makefile:6: obj_dir/Vtestbench] Error 1
```

PS: I tried without queues and it still does not work, it appears that type casting does not work in verilator using with operator ?
